#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; is an application for Interactive Geometry. It's intended to serve two "
"purposes:"
msgstr "&kig; je aplikacija za interaktivno geometrijo. Služi dvema namenoma:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allow students to interactively explore mathematical figures and concepts "
"using the computer."
msgstr ""
"Študentom omogoči interaktivno raziskovanje matematičnih številk in "
"konceptov z uporabo računalnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Serve as a <acronym>WYSIWYG</acronym> tool for drawing mathematical figures "
"and including them in other documents."
msgstr ""
"Služi kot <acronym>WYSIWYG</acronym> orodje za risanje matematičnih številk "
"in njihovo vključitev v druge dokumente."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can report problems in &kig; using the internal bug reporting tool "
"(<menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>Report Bug...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>)."
msgstr ""
"Težave lahko prijavite v &kig; z uporabo internega orodja za poročanje o "
"napakah (<menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu><guimenuitem>Prijavi napako...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since &kig; supports macros and the construction of loci, it allows for some "
"rather advanced macros to be defined. If you have created an interesting "
"macro, which you think might be useful for other people, please open a "
"review request for the change, so that it can be evaluated for the inclusion "
"in the distribution (if you do this, it will be licensed under the terms of "
"&kig;'s license, the <ulink url=\"https://www.gnu.org/licenses/licenses."
"html#GPL\">GPL</ulink>, so that other people can freely use and adapt it)."
msgstr ""
"Ker &kig; podpira makre in konstrukcijo lokusov, omogoča definiranje "
"nekaterih precej naprednih makrov. Če ste ustvarili zanimiv makro, za "
"katerega menite, da bi lahko bil uporaben za druge ljudi, odprite zahtevo za "
"pregled spremembe, da bo lahko ocenjen za vključitev v distribucijo (če to "
"storite, bo licenciran pod pogoje licence &kig;, <ulink url=\"https://www."
"gnu.org/licenses/licenses.html#GPL\">GPL</ulink>, tako da jo lahko drugi "
"ljudje prosto uporabljajo in prilagajajo)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "Basic usage"
msgstr "Osnovna uporaba"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Constructing Objects"
msgstr "Konstruiranje predmetov"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Constructing points"
msgstr "Gradnja točk"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can construct points in several ways:"
msgstr "Točke lahko zgradite na več načinov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <menuchoice><guimenu>Objects</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Points</"
"guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>Point</guimenuitem></menuchoice> from the menubar "
"or press the appropriate button in the toolbar. You can then construct a "
"point by clicking at the desired position in the window."
msgstr ""
"Izberite <menuchoice><guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Točke</"
"guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>Točka</guimenuitem></menuchoice> v menijski vrstici "
"ali pritisnite ustrezen gumb v orodni vrstici. Nato lahko sestavite točko s "
"klikom na želeno mesto v oknu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press the &Shift; key to activate a snap raster mode which allows you to set "
"any point in a construction exactly to points of the grid."
msgstr ""
"Pritisnite tipko &Shift; za aktiviranje rastrskega načina pripenjanja, ki "
"vam omogoča, da katero koli točko v konstrukciji nastavite natančno na točke "
"mreže."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Actually, this works the same way for constructing other objects as well: "
"click on the desired menubar entry or toolbar button and select the "
"necessary items to construct the object."
msgstr ""
"Pravzaprav to deluje na enak način tudi za konstruiranje drugih objektov: "
"kliknite želeni vnos v menijski vrstici ali gumb orodne vrstice in izberite "
"potrebne elemente za konstruiranje predmeta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since you often need to construct points, simply clicking somewhere in the "
"screen with the &MMB; will construct a point for you, without going to a "
"menu or button."
msgstr ""
"Ker morate pogosto konstruirati točke, preprosto kliknite nekje na zaslonu z "
"&MMB; bo za vas sestavil točko, ne da bi šel v meni ali gumb."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can construct points while you are building other objects in the "
"background, optionally selecting them for the object you are building. For "
"more on this, see <xref linkend=\"constructing-other-objects\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Točke lahko gradite, medtem ko gradite druge objekte v ozadju, po želji pa "
"jih izberete za objekt, ki ga gradite. Za več o tem glejte <xref linkend="
"\"constructing-other-objects\"/>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>A point has been constructed</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Točka je bila zgrajena</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>A point has been constructed</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Točka je bila zgrajena</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid "Constructing Other Objects"
msgstr "Gradnja drugih predmetov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Constructing objects other than points is usually done by selecting the "
"appropriate entry in the <guimenu>Objects</guimenu> menu, or by clicking on "
"one of the toolbar buttons."
msgstr ""
"Konstruiranje predmetov, ki niso točke, običajno poteka z izbiro ustreznega "
"vnosa v meniju <guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu> ali s klikom na enega od gumbov v "
"orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Constructing a circle</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Konstruiranje kroga</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:174 index.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Constructing a circle</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Konstruiranje kroga</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This will start the construction of the chosen object type. All of these "
"types require arguments. For example, if you selected to construct a circle "
"by center and point, you will need to give two points: one for the center, "
"and one for the point on the circle."
msgstr ""
"S tem se začne gradnja izbrane vrste predmeta. Vse te vrste zahtevajo "
"argumente. Na primer, če ste izbrali sestavo kroga s središčem in točko, "
"boste morali podati dve točki: eno za središče in eno za točko na krogu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These arguments are objects too, which can also be selected, simply by "
"clicking on them. When you move the cursor over an argument you want to use "
"to construct an object, a preliminary image will be shown of the object, so "
"you will know what it will look like. For objects that require points as "
"arguments, you can place a new point at the current cursor position and "
"select it by clicking the &LMB;."
msgstr ""
"Tudi ti argumenti so predmeti, ki jih je mogoče tudi izbrati s preprostim "
"klikom nanje. Ko premaknete kazalec nad argument, ki ga želite uporabiti za "
"sestavo predmeta, se bo prikazala predhodna slika predmeta, tako da boste "
"vedeli, kako bo videti. Za predmete, ki zahtevajo točke kot argumente, lahko "
"postavite novo točko na trenutni položaj kazalke in jo izberete s klikom "
"&LMB;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can always cancel the construction of the new object by pressing the "
"&Esc; button or by clicking on the &nbsp;<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> "
"<imagedata fileref=\"process-stop.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Cancel Construction</guibutton> button on the "
"toolbar."
msgstr ""
"Konstrukcijo novega predmeta lahko kadar koli prekličete s pritiskom na "
"&Esc; ali s klikom na gumb &nbsp;<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> "
"<imagedata fileref=\"process-stop.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Prekliči gradnjo</guibutton> na orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:200
#, no-c-format
msgid "Constructing a circle."
msgstr "Konstruiranje kroga."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:215
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selecting Objects"
msgstr "Izbiranje predmetov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:216
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selecting objects can be done in two ways:"
msgstr "Izbira predmetov je možna na dva načina:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Simply clicking on an object causes that object to be selected, clearing the "
"current selection. If you want to select multiple objects simultaneously, "
"hold down the &Ctrl; key while clicking on an object."
msgstr ""
"Preprost klik na predmet povzroči, da je predmet izbran in počiščen trenutni "
"izbor. Če želite izbrati več predmetov hkrati, držite tipko &Ctrl; med "
"klikom na predmet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By clicking and dragging on an empty spot on the screen, you can select all "
"objects within the rectangle that is created. This action will clear the "
"current selection. As in the previous case, holding down the &Ctrl; key "
"allows you to keep the current selection."
msgstr ""
"S klikom in vlečenjem na prazno mesto na zaslonu lahko izberete vse predmete "
"v pravokotniku, ki je ustvarjen. To dejanje bo počistilo trenutno izbiro. "
"Kot v prejšnjem primeru, držite &Ctrl; tipka vam omogoča, da obdržite "
"trenutno izbiro."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you have more than one object under the mouse (indicated by "
"<guilabel>Which object?</guilabel> in the statusbar and at the mouse "
"cursor), you can easily choose which object select or add to the current "
"selection. Click with the &LMB;, while holding the &Shift; key or click the "
"&RMB;, to have a popup with all the objects under the mouse. Then, you can "
"select the object you need. As said before, the behaviour of the &Ctrl; key "
"will affect the selection."
msgstr ""
"Ko imate pod miško več kot en predmet (označen z <guilabel>Kateri predmet?</"
"guilabel> v statusni vrstici in na miškinem kazalcu), lahko preprosto "
"izberete, kateri predmet želite izbrati ali dodati trenutnemu izboru. "
"Kliknite z &LMB;, medtem ko držite &Shift; tipko ali kliknite &RMB;, da se "
"prikaže pojavno okno z vsemi predmeti pod miško. Nato lahko izberete "
"predmet, ki ga potrebujete. Kot je bilo že omenjeno, vedenje tipke &Ctrl; "
"vpliva na izbiro."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Selecting objects</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Izbiranje predmetov</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Selecting objects</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Izbiranje predmetov</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:261
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving Objects"
msgstr "Premikanje predmetov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To move objects, you must first <link linkend=\"selecting-objects\">select</"
"link> them."
msgstr ""
"Če želite premakniti predmete, jih morate najprej <link linkend=\"selecting-"
"objects\">izbrati</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the objects you want to move are selected, you can start moving them by "
"&LMB; clicking and dragging any one of them. When you are done, simply "
"release the &LMB;."
msgstr ""
"Ko so predmeti izbrani, ki jih želite premakniti, jih lahko začnete "
"premikati z &LMB; klikanje in vlečenje katerega koli od njih. Ko končate, "
"preprosto spustite &LMB;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:271
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For some types of objects (especially when defined by complicated loci), "
"moving them can be slow on old hardware. This is unfortunate, but "
"inevitable, given the calculations involved."
msgstr ""
"Pri nekaterih vrstah predmetov (zlasti če so definirani z zapletenimi "
"lokusi) je lahko premikanje na stari strojni opremi počasno. To je "
"obžalovanja vredno, vendar neizogibno glede na vključene izračune."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you &RMB; click one of the selected objects, and choose "
"<guimenuitem>Move</guimenuitem>, moving the mouse will move the object. When "
"the object is moved to the desired position, another &LMB; click will stop "
"the moving of the object."
msgstr ""
"Če &RMB; kliknite enega od izbranih predmetov in izberite "
"<guimenuitem>Premakni</guimenuitem>, premikanje miške bo premaknilo predmet. "
"Ko je predmet premaknjen na želeni položaj, bo drugi klik &LMB; ustavil "
"premikanje predmeta."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Deleting objects"
msgstr "Brisanje predmetov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Deleting objects is done by first <link linkend=\"selecting-objects"
"\">selecting</link> them, and next doing either of these:"
msgstr ""
"Predmete izbrišete tako, da jih najprej <link linkend=\"selecting-objects"
"\">izberete</link> in nato naredite kar koli od tega:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid "Press the &Del; key."
msgstr "Pritisnite tipko &Del;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press the &nbsp;<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"edit-"
"delete.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> "
"<guibutton>Delete Objects</guibutton> button on the toolbar."
msgstr ""
"V orodni vrstici pritisnite &nbsp;<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> "
"<imagedata fileref=\"edit-delete.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Izbriši predmete</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<mousebutton>Right</mousebutton>-click on one of the objects, and select "
"<guimenuitem>Delete</guimenuitem> in the <link linkend=\"objects-context-"
"menus\">context menu</link> that appears."
msgstr ""
"<mousebutton>Z desnim gumbom miške</mousebutton>-kliknite na enega od "
"predmetov in izberite <guimenuitem>Izbriši</guimenuitem> v <link linkend="
"\"objects-context-menus\">kontekstnem meniju</link>, ki se prikaže."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "Showing and hiding objects"
msgstr "Prikazovanje in skrivanje predmetov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &kig;, objects can be hidden. This is done by selecting the objects, "
"&RMB; clicking one of them, and selecting <guimenuitem>Hide</guimenuitem> in "
"the <link linkend=\"objects-context-menus\">context menu</link> that appears."
msgstr ""
"V &kig; lahko predmete skrijete. To storite tako, da izberete predmete, "
"&RMB; kliknite enega od njih in izberite <guimenuitem>Skrij</guimenuitem> v "
"<link linkend=\"objects-context-menus\">kontekstnem meniju</link>, ki se "
"prikaže."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To unhide the objects, use the <menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Unhide All</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. This will unhide "
"all currently hidden objects."
msgstr ""
"Če želite razkriti predmete, uporabite <menuchoice><guimenu>Uredi</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Razkrij vse</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. S tem boste "
"razkrili vse trenutno skrite predmete."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:329
#, no-c-format
msgid "Night Vision"
msgstr "Nočni vid"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Night Vision is a particular way of working with hidden objects. When you "
"have to move or change something in one or more object but without unhiding "
"all the hidden objects you have, then the night vision mode will be of "
"benefit to you."
msgstr ""
"Nočni vid je poseben način dela s skritimi predmeti. Ko morate nekaj "
"premakniti ali spremeniti v enem ali več predmetih, vendar ne da bi razkrili "
"vse skrite predmete, ki jih imate, vam bo način nočnega vida koristil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Basically, it allows you to see the hidden objects as if they were visible, "
"so that you can manipulate them as you would normally. In Night Vision mode, "
"the hidden objects will be visible with a grey colour."
msgstr ""
"V bistvu vam omogoča, da vidite skrite predmete, kot da bi bili vidni, tako "
"da lahko z njimi manipulirate kot običajno. V načinu nočnega vida bodo "
"skriti predmeti vidni v sivi barvi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To toggle the night vision mode, use <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Wear Infrared Glasses</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Za preklop načina nočnega vida uporabite <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Nosim infrardeča očala</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid "Undo/Redo"
msgstr "Razveljavi/Uveljavi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &kig;, you can undo almost any change you make in the document. Just use "
"the <guiicon>Undo</guiicon>/<guiicon>Redo</guiicon> buttons on the toolbar, "
"the <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> menu or the appropriate keyboard shortcuts."
msgstr ""
"V &kig; lahko razveljavite skoraj vse spremembe, ki jih naredite v "
"dokumentu. Preprosto uporabite gumba <guiicon>Razveljavi</guiicon>/"
"<guiicon>Uveljavi</guiicon> v orodni vrstici, meni <guimenu>Uredi</guimenu> "
"ali ustrezne bližnjice na tipkovnici."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:361
#, no-c-format
msgid "Full Screen Mode"
msgstr "Celozaslonski način"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; also has a Full Screen mode. To use it, click the appropriate button "
"on the toolbar, or select <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Full Screen Mode</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"&kig; ima tudi celozaslonski način. Če ga želite uporabiti, kliknite "
"ustrezni gumb v orodni vrstici ali izberite <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Celozaslonski način</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To leave Full Screen mode, &RMB; click the screen at a place where there is "
"no object present, and select <guimenuitem>Exit Full Screen Mode</"
"guimenuitem>, or press the shortcut <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;"
"<keycap>F</keycap></keycombo>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite zapustiti celozaslonski način, &RMB; kliknite zaslon na mestu, "
"kjer ni nobenega predmeta, in izberite <guimenuitem>Izhod iz celozaslonskega "
"načina</guimenuitem> ali pritisnite bližnjico <keycombo action=\"simul"
"\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>F</keycap ></keycombo>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kig; Object Types"
msgstr "&kig; vrste predmetov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; supports a rather large number of object types. Please note that not "
"all of the available object types are shown in the toolbars: there are some "
"objects that you can only construct via the <guimenu>Objects</guimenu> menu "
"in the menu bar. Of course, as with all &kde; applications, the contents of "
"the toolbars are configurable. Try out the <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure Toolbars...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> option "
"if you want to do this."
msgstr ""
"&kig; podpira precej veliko število vrst objektov. Upoštevajte, da v orodnih "
"vrsticah niso prikazane vse razpoložljive vrste predmetov: nekatere predmete "
"lahko sestavite samo prek menija <guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu> v menijski "
"vrstici. Seveda, kot pri vseh &kde; aplikacij, je vsebina orodnih vrstic "
"nastavljiva. Preizkusite možnost <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj orodne vrstice ...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>, če želite to narediti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:395
#, no-c-format
msgid "Advanced Usage"
msgstr "Napredna uporaba"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:397
#, no-c-format
msgid "Context Menus"
msgstr "Kontekstni meniji"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; has context menus for its objects. Try &RMB; clicking on an object in "
"order to see a context menu appear. There are many options: for constructing "
"other objects, setting colours, pen width, style, and even hiding, moving or "
"deleting objects. Some objects have options of their own (&eg; you can "
"redefine certain points to be constrained to a line if they previously "
"weren't, &etc;). These options should be very straightforward to understand."
msgstr ""
"&kig; ima kontekstne menije za svoje predmete. Poskusite &RMB; klik na "
"predmet, da se prikaže kontekstni meni. Obstaja veliko možnosti: za sestavo "
"drugih predmetov, nastavitev barv, širine pisala, sloga in celo skrivanje, "
"premikanje ali brisanje predmetov. Nekateri predmeti imajo lastne možnosti "
"(&eg; določene točke lahko na novo definirate tako, da bodo omejene na črto, "
"če prej niso bile &etc;). Te možnosti bi morale biti zelo enostavne za "
"razumevanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some of the actions in the context menu of an object need another defined "
"object as reference, for example:"
msgstr ""
"Nekatera dejanja v kontekstnem meniju predmeta potrebujejo drug definiran "
"predmet kot referenco, na primer:"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:414
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rotate a shape a specific number of degrees around a point"
msgstr "Zasukajte obliko za določeno število stopinj okoli točke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click on <menuchoice><guimenu>Objects</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Angles</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Angle by Three Points</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> "
"and make your desired angle of rotation somewhere in the &kig; window, "
"generally in an unobtrusive place. If desired, right click on the angle and "
"click on <menuchoice><guisubmenu>Add Text Label</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Angle in Degrees</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Kliknite na <menuchoice><guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Koti</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Kot za tri točke</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> in "
"nastavite želeni kot sukanja nekje v &kig; okno, običajno na neopaznem "
"mestu. Če želite, z desno miškino tipko kliknite kot in kliknite "
"<menuchoice><guisubmenu>Dodaj besedilno oznako</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Kot "
"v stopinjah</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click with the &RMB; on the angle and select <guimenuitem>Set Size</"
"guimenuitem> and insert the new size for this angle in the dialog."
msgstr ""
"Kliknite z &RMB; na kot in izberite <guimenuitem>Nastavi velikost</"
"guimenuitem> ter v pogovorno okno vstavite novo velikost za ta kot."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click on <guimenu>Objects</guimenu> menu and construct your desired object."
msgstr ""
"Kliknite na meni <guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu> in sestavite želeni predmet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right click on your shape, and select on <menuchoice><guisubmenu>Transform</"
"guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>Rotate</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Desni klik na vašo obliko in izberite <menuchoice><guisubmenu>Preoblikuj</"
"guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>Zavrti</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:429
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set your desired point of rotation."
msgstr "Nastavite želeno točko vrtenja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click on your angle."
msgstr "Kliknite na svoj kot."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:431
#, no-c-format
msgid "Your shape is rotated!"
msgstr "Vaša oblika je zavrtena!"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:448
#, no-c-format
msgid "Translate an object"
msgstr "Premakni predmet"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click on <menuchoice><guimenu>Objects</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Vectors &amp; "
"Segments</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Vector</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> and "
"construct the object by selecting the start and end point somewhere in the "
"&kig; window."
msgstr ""
"Kliknite <menuchoice><guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Vektorji &amp; "
"Segmenti</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Vektor</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> in "
"sestavite objekt tako, da izberete začetno in končno točko nekje v &kig; "
"oknu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To adjust length and direction of the vector you have to edit its start and "
"end point. Select them and choose <guimenuitem>Set Coordinate...</"
"guimenuitem> in the context menu."
msgstr ""
"Če želite prilagoditi dolžino in smer vektorja, morate urediti njegovo "
"začetno in končno točko. Izberite jih in v kontekstnem meniju izberite "
"<guimenuitem>Nastavi koordinate...</guimenuitem>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click on <guimenu>Objects</guimenu> and construct your desired object."
msgstr "Kliknite <guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu> in konstruirajte želeni predmet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:460
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right click on your object, and select on <menuchoice><guisubmenu>Transform</"
"guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>Translate</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Desni klik na vaš predmet in izberite <menuchoice><guisubmenu>Pretvori</"
"guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>Premakni</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:462
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the vector to translate by."
msgstr "Izberite vektor po katerem želite premakniti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Document context menus"
msgstr "Kontekstni meniji dokumenta"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<mousebutton>Right</mousebutton>-clicking on the document (&ie; not on an "
"object) will present a popup that you can use to start constructing a new "
"object, change the coordinate system used, show hidden objects, zoom in and "
"zoom out of the document and switch to the full screen mode."
msgstr ""
"<mousebutton>Desni</mousebutton>-klik na dokument (&ie; ne na predmet) bo "
"prikazal pojavno okno, ki ga lahko uporabite za začetek izdelave novega "
"predmeta, spremembo uporabljenega koordinatnega sistema, prikaz skritih "
"predmetov, približevanje in povečevanje iz dokumenta in preklopite na "
"celozaslonski način."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:481
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining Macros"
msgstr "Definiranje makrov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One of the more advanced features in &kig; is its support for macros. This "
"allows you to define new types of objects from other ones which are defined "
"already."
msgstr ""
"Ena izmed bolj naprednih funkcij v &kig; je njegova podpora za makre. To vam "
"omogoča, da definirate nove tipe predmetov iz drugih, ki so že definirani."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example: Suppose you want to make a macro for constructing a circle from "
"three points on it. You would input three points, then construct some "
"perpendiculars and midpoints until you find the center. Now you can use the "
"existing <guimenuitem>Circle by Center &amp; Point</guimenuitem> command "
"(using one of the three points as the point for this command). The following "
"image should make this a bit more clear:"
msgstr ""
"Na primer: Recimo, da želite narediti makro za sestavo kroga iz treh točk na "
"njem. Vnesli bi tri točke, nato pa zgradili nekaj navpičnic in središč, "
"dokler ne najdete središča. Zdaj lahko uporabite obstoječi <guimenuitem>Krog "
"iz središča &amp; Ukaz Točka</guimenuitem> (z uporabo ene od treh točk kot "
"točke za ta ukaz). Naslednja slika naj bo to nekoliko bolj razjasnila:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Test running macros</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Preizkus izvajanja makrov</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:503
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Test running macros</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Preizkus izvajanja makrov</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:508
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next comes defining the macro. Select the <menuchoice><guimenu>Types</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>New Macro...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item, or "
"click on the &nbsp;<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref="
"\"system-run.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> "
"<guibutton>New Macro...</guibutton> button on the toolbar. A wizard will "
"appear and ask you to select the given objects. In our example, these are "
"the three points. Select the three points (click on them to select, click "
"again to unselect) and click the <guibutton>Next</guibutton> button to "
"continue. Finally, select the last objects (only the circle in our example)."
msgstr ""
"Sledi definiranje makra. Izberite menijski element "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Vrste</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Nov makro...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> ali kliknite gumb &nbsp;"
"<inlinemediaobject><imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"system -run.png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Nov makro...</"
"guibutton> v orodni vrstici. Prikaže se čarovnik, ki vas bo pozval, da "
"izberete dane predmete. V našem primeru so to tri točke. Izberite tri točke "
"(kliknite nanje za izbiro, znova kliknite za preklic) in kliknite gumb "
"<guibutton>Naprej</guibutton> za nadaljevanje. Na koncu izberite še zadnje "
"predmete (v našem primeru samo krog)."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:521
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The macro wizard</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Čarovnik za makro</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:527
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The macro wizard</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Čarovnik za makro</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the previous steps are completed, click the <guibutton>Next</"
"guibutton> button to continue. Enter a name and optionally a description for "
"your new type, and click the <guibutton>Finish</guibutton> button. Your "
"macro type is now finished."
msgstr ""
"Ko so prejšnji koraki končani, za nadaljevanje kliknite gumb "
"<guibutton>Naprej</guibutton>. Vnesite ime in po želji opis za svojo novo "
"vrsto in kliknite gumb <guibutton>Dokončaj</guibutton>. Vaša vrsta makra je "
"zdaj končana."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:539
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use the new macro type, click its button on the toolbar or use the "
"<guimenu>Objects</guimenu> menu. Constructing a macro object is just like "
"constructing any other object."
msgstr ""
"Če želite uporabiti novo vrsto makra, kliknite njegov gumb v orodni vrstici "
"ali uporabite meni <guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu>. Konstruiranje makro objekta "
"je tako kot konstruiranje katerega koli drugega objekta."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Using your new type</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Uporaba vaše nove vrste</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:551
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Using your new type</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Uporaba vaše nove vrste</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:558
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working with types"
msgstr "Delo z vrstami"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:559
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As you saw in the previous chapter, &kig; allows you to create your own "
"objects. &kig; also makes sure that once you have created an object, it is "
"saved on exit and loaded on startup. You do not have to manually save or "
"load macro definitions. However, &kig; does allow you to do more with the "
"macros. If you select <menuchoice><guimenu>Types</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Manage Types...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> from the "
"menu, you will see a dialog where you can edit your types. It allows you to "
"modify the existent types, delete types that are no longer used, export them "
"to a file, or even load them from another file."
msgstr ""
"Kot ste videli v prejšnjem poglavju, &kig; omogoča ustvarjanje lastnih "
"predmetov. &kig; prav tako poskrbi, da se objekt, ko ste ga ustvarili, "
"shrani ob izhodu in naloži ob zagonu. Ni vam treba ročno shranjevati ali "
"nalagati definicij makrov. Vendar vam &kig; omogoča, da naredite več z "
"makri. Če v meniju izberete <menuchoice><guimenu>Vrste</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Upravljanje vrst...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, boste "
"videli pogovorno okno, kjer lahko uredite svoje vrste. Omogoča vam "
"spreminjanje obstoječih vrst, brisanje vrst, ki se ne uporabljajo več, izvoz "
"v datoteko ali celo nalaganje iz druge datoteke."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:572
#, no-c-format
msgid "Edit Types Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno za urejanje vrst"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:578
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Edit Types Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno za urejanje vrst"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:585
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text labels"
msgstr "Besedilne oznake"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; allows you to add text labels to a construction. This is very useful "
"for adding names, explanations or other text to constructions. &kig; can "
"also display variable information about objects (also known as "
"<quote>properties</quote>)."
msgstr ""
"&kig; omogoča dodajanje besedilnih oznak konstrukciji. To je zelo uporabno "
"za dodajanje imen, razlag ali drugega besedila konstrukcijam. &kig; lahko "
"prikaže tudi spremenljive informacije o objektih (znane tudi kot "
"<quote>lastnosti</quote>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:592
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To start constructing a text label, simply press the &nbsp;"
"<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"kig_text.png\" format="
"\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Text Label</"
"guibutton> button in the &kig; toolbar or select the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Objects</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Other</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Text Label</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Če želite začeti sestavljati besedilno oznako, preprosto pritisnite &nbsp;"
"<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"kig_text.png\" format="
"\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Besedilna oznaka</"
"guibutton > v meniju &kig; orodni vrstici ali izberite menijsko postavko "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Drugo</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Besedilna oznaka</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next, you have to choose a location for the text label. You can either just "
"select a random location on the screen, or choose to <quote>attach</quote> "
"the label to an object."
msgstr ""
"Nato morate izbrati lokacijo za besedilno oznako. Lahko samo izberete "
"naključno mesto na zaslonu ali izberete, da <quote>pripnete</quote> oznako "
"na predmet."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Attaching a label to a circle...</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pripenjanje oznake krogu...</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:612
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Attaching a label to a circle...</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pripenjanje oznake krogu...</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:616
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you have selected where to put the label, the text label dialog "
"appears. Here, you can type in the text that you want in the new label, and "
"click <guibutton>Finish</guibutton>. You should now see the label in your "
"document."
msgstr ""
"Ko izberete mesto za oznako, se prikaže pogovorno okno z besedilno oznako. "
"Tukaj lahko vnesete besedilo, ki ga želite v novo oznako, in kliknete "
"<guibutton>Dokončaj</guibutton>. Zdaj bi morali videti oznako v dokumentu."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:623
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Text Label Dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno besedilne oznake</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:629
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Text Label Dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno besedilne oznake</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The previous example was a simple one, and limited to just text. However, "
"there is also support for showing variable information about objects in a "
"label (&eg; you can construct a label with the text <quote>This segment is "
"%1 units long.</quote> where <token>%1</token> would be dynamically replaced "
"with the length of a specific segment)."
msgstr ""
"Prejšnji primer je bil preprost in omejen samo na besedilo. Obstaja pa tudi "
"podpora za prikaz spremenljivih informacij o predmetih v oznaki (&eg; lahko "
"sestavite oznako z besedilom <quote>Ta segment je dolg %1 enot.</quote> kjer "
"je <token>%1</token > bi bila dinamično nadomeščena z dolžino določenega "
"segmenta)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:641
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To do this, enter a text with a number of placeholders ( <token>%1</token>, "
"<token>%2</token> &etc;) in it. Then, press the <guibutton>Next</guibutton> "
"button to continue. If you want to change the text or variables later, you "
"can go back using the <guibutton>Back</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite to narediti, vnesite besedilo s številnimi ogradami ( <token>%1</"
"token>, <token>%2</token> &etc;.) v njem. Nato za nadaljevanje pritisnite "
"gumb <guibutton>Naprej</guibutton>. Če želite pozneje spremeniti besedilo "
"ali spremenljivke, se lahko vrnete nazaj z gumbom <guibutton>Nazaj</"
"guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:648
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The wizard now shows the text you entered with all placeholders replaced by "
"something like <guilabel>argument 1</guilabel>. Selecting the property "
"connected to a certain argument is done by first clicking on the argument in "
"question. Then click on the object that you need and that has this property, "
"and then select the property itself in the popup menu that appears. For "
"instance, in the example above, you would click <guilabel>argument 1</"
"guilabel>, click on the correct segment in the main &kig; window, and select "
"the property <guilabel>Length</guilabel>. Afterwards, you can fill in the "
"rest of the variable parts, or select another property for one of the "
"variable parts if you wish to change it. When you are ready, click the "
"<guibutton>Finish</guibutton> button to complete the construction of the "
"text label."
msgstr ""
"Čarovnik zdaj prikaže besedilo, ki ste ga vnesli, z vsemi ogradami, "
"zamenjanimi z nečim, kot je <guilabel>argument 1</guilabel>. Izbira "
"lastnosti, povezane z določenim argumentom, se izvede tako, da najprej "
"kliknete na zadevni argument. Nato kliknite predmet, ki ga potrebujete in "
"ima to lastnost, nato pa v pojavnem meniju, ki se prikaže, izberite samo "
"lastnost. Na primer, v zgornjem primeru bi kliknili <guilabel>argument 1</"
"guilabel>, kliknite pravilen segment v glavnem &kig; in izberite lastnost "
"<guilabel >Dolžina</guilabel >. Nato lahko izpolnite preostale variabilne "
"dele ali izberete drugo lastnost za enega od variabilnih delov, če jo želite "
"spremeniti. Ko ste pripravljeni, kliknite gumb <guibutton>Dokončaj</"
"guibutton>, da dokončate izdelavo besedilne oznake."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:666
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Selecting a property for a variable part</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Izbira lastnosti za variabilni del</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:675
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Selecting a property for a variable part</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Izbira lastnosti za variabilni del</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:682
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loci"
msgstr "Loci"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:683
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; supports the use of loci. A locus is mathematically defined as the set "
"of all points or lines that satisfy or are determined by specific "
"conditions; as in <quote>the locus of points equidistant from a given point "
"is a circle</quote>. Let's look at an example of how to use loci in &kig;:"
msgstr ""
"&kig; podpira uporabo lokusov. Geografsko mesto je matematično opredeljeno "
"kot niz vseh točk ali črt, ki zadovoljujejo ali so določene s posebnimi "
"pogoji; kot v <quote>mesto točk, ki so enako oddaljene od dane točke, je "
"krog</quote>. Oglejmo si primer, kako uporabiti lokus v &kig;:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider the following geometrical construction: We draw a circle, and a "
"point that can move only along its circumference (construct this point by "
"positioning the cursor on a circle, and clicking the &MMB;. If you then try "
"to move the resulting point, you'll see that you cannot move it off the "
"circle). Then, we draw a segment from that point to the center of the "
"circle, and the midpoint of that segment."
msgstr ""
"Razmislite o naslednji geometrijski konstrukciji: Narišemo krog in točko, ki "
"se lahko premika samo vzdolž njegovega oboda (konstruirajte to točko tako, "
"da postavite kazalec na krog in kliknete &MMB;. Če nato poskušate premakniti "
"nastalo točko, boste videli, da ga ne morete premakniti iz kroga). Nato "
"narišemo odsek od te točke do središča kroga in središče tega odseka."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:700
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>A simple construction using a locus</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Preprosta konstrukcija z uporabo lokusa</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:708
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>A simple construction using a locus</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Preprosta konstrukcija z uporabo lokusa</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:712
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now if you move the point that is constrained to the circle, you'll see that "
"the second point moves along with it. If you were to hold a pen at the "
"second point, and move the first point around the entire circle, a new "
"circle, half the size of the other would be drawn. The path that the second "
"point travels while the first one moves around the circle is its locus."
msgstr ""
"Če zdaj premaknete točko, ki je omejena na krog, boste videli, da se druga "
"točka premika skupaj z njo. Če bi držali pisalo na drugi točki in prvo točko "
"premikali po celotnem krogu, bi bil narisan nov krog, ki bi bil za polovico "
"manjši od drugega. Pot, ki jo prepotuje druga točka, medtem ko se prva "
"premika po krogu, je njen geometrijski lokus."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:720
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Actually constructing the locus of a point is very easy. Click the &nbsp;"
"<inlinemediaobject><imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"locus.png\" format="
"\"PNG\"/> </imageobject></inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Locus</guibutton> "
"button in the toolbar, or select the <menuchoice><guimenu>Objects</guimenu> "
"<guisubmenu>Other</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Locus</guimenuitem></menuchoice> "
"menu item. Then select the constrained point as the moving point (the text "
"<guilabel>Moving Point</guilabel> will appear as you move the mouse over "
"it), and the other as the <guilabel>Dependent point</guilabel>. The locus of "
"the dependent point will then be drawn."
msgstr ""
"Konstruiranje geometrijskega lokusa točke je pravzaprav zelo enostavno. V "
"orodni vrstici kliknite &nbsp;<inlinemediaobject><imageobject> <imagedata "
"fileref=\"locus.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject></inlinemediaobject> "
"<guibutton>Lokus</guibutton> ali izberite <menuchoice><guimenu>Predmeti</"
"guimenu> <guisubmenu>Drugo</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Menijski element</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Nato izberite omejeno točko kot premikajočo se "
"točko (besedilo <guilabel>Premikajoča se točka</guilabel> se prikaže, ko "
"premaknete miško nad njo), drugo pa kot <guilabel>Odvisno točko</guilabel>. "
"Nato bo narisano geometrijsko mesto odvisne točke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:736
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scripting"
msgstr "Skriptiranje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:737
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; allows you to create custom types in the Python scripting language. "
"This is a very advanced feature, and I know of only one other Interactive "
"Geometry program that has a similar functionality (the <acronym>GNOME</"
"acronym> program &drgeo;)."
msgstr ""
"&kig; omogoča ustvarjanje vrst po meri v skriptnem jeziku Python. To je zelo "
"napredna funkcija in poznam le še en program za interaktivno geometrijo, ki "
"ima podobno funkcionalnost (program <acronym>GNOME</acronym> &drgeo;)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:743
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Python Scripting in &kig; basically allows you to create your own objects "
"from certain parent objects. For example, if you are a math teacher, and you "
"have some fancy way of calculating an interesting point on a conic, then "
"instead of messing with complex constructions and macros, you could just "
"write down in Python code how the point is to be calculated and then &kig; "
"will show it for you."
msgstr ""
"Python skriptiranje v &kig; vam v bistvu omogoča ustvarjanje lastnih "
"predmetov iz določenih nadrejenih predmetov. Na primer, če ste učitelj "
"matematike in imate kakšen domiseln način za izračun zanimive točke na "
"stožnici, potem namesto da se ubadate z zapletenimi konstrukcijami in makri, "
"lahko preprosto zapišete v kodo Python, kako naj se točka izračuna in nato "
"vam ga bo  &kig; pokazal."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:752
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Suppose you were not aware of the &kig; built-in type <quote>Mid Point</"
"quote>, and you wanted to show the midpoint of two given points. You would "
"then click on the &nbsp;<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref="
"\"text-x-python3.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> "
"<guibutton>Python Script</guibutton> button in the toolbar, or select "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Objects</guimenu><guisubmenu>Other</guisubmenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Python Script</guimenuitem></menuchoice> from the menubar. You "
"are then presented with a wizard that allows you to proceed."
msgstr ""
"Recimo, da niste vedeli za &kig; vgrajen tip <quote>Srednja točka</quote> in "
"želeli ste prikazati sredino dveh danih točk. Nato bi kliknili &nbsp;"
"<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"text-x-python3.png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Skript "
"Python</guibutton > v orodni vrstici ali izberite "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Predmeti</guimenu><guisubmenu>Drugo</guisubmenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Python skript</guimenuitem></menuchoice> v menijski vrstici. "
"Nato se vam prikaže čarovnik, ki vam omogoča nadaljevanje."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:764
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Script Object Wizard</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Čarovnik za predmet skripta</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:770
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Script Object Wizard</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Čarovnik za predmet skripta</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:774
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first thing you have to do is select the arguments for the script "
"object. In our example, this means the two points of which we want to show "
"the midpoint. Select them in the &kig; main window, and click "
"<guibutton>Next</guibutton> to proceed."
msgstr ""
"Prva stvar, ki jo morate storiti, je, da izberete argumente za predmet "
"skripta. V našem primeru to pomeni dve točki, katerih središče želimo "
"prikazati. Izberite jih v glavnem oknu &kig; in za nadaljevanje kliknite "
"<guibutton>Naprej</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:780
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you are presented with a text edit box where you can enter the code for "
"you script object. Template code and some comments are already in place. It "
"is important to make sure that your code is valid Python code. People "
"familiar with Python will notice that we are actually defining a Python "
"function called <function>calc</function>. It is therefore necessary to "
"adhere to the Python rules for defining functions. For example, every line "
"of the function should start with a tab. The first line not starting with a "
"tab ends the definition of the function."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj se vam prikaže polje za urejanje besedila, v katerega lahko vnesete "
"kodo za svoj predmet skripta. Koda predloge in nekateri komentarji so že "
"pripravljeni. Pomembno je zagotoviti, da je vaša koda veljavna koda Python. "
"Ljudje, ki poznajo Python, bodo opazili, da dejansko definiramo funkcijo "
"Python, imenovano <function>calc</function>. Zato je potrebno upoštevati "
"pravila Pythona za definiranje funkcij. Na primer, vsaka vrstica funkcije se "
"mora začeti z tabulatorjem. Prva vrstica, ki se ne začne s tabulatorjem, "
"konča definicijo funkcije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:791
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Python function that we want to define is called <function>calc</"
"function>, and in our case it accepts two arguments. These are the objects "
"you have selected as arguments in the previous screen. You need as many "
"arguments as you have selected there. They are called <parameter>arg1</"
"parameter> and <parameter>arg2</parameter>, but you can change their names "
"to something more meaningful if you want."
msgstr ""
"Funkcija Python, ki jo želimo definirati, se imenuje <function>calc</"
"function> in v našem primeru sprejme dva argumenta. To so predmeti, ki ste "
"jih izbrali kot argumente na prejšnjem zaslonu. Potrebujete toliko "
"argumentov, kot ste jih tam izbrali. Imenujejo se <parameter>arg1</"
"parameter> in <parameter>arg2</parameter>, a lahko spremenite njihova imena "
"v bolj smiselna, če želite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:800
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the function, you can do all sorts of calculations that you deem "
"necessary, using the two arguments if needed. You should return the object "
"you want to define. In our case, this is a <classname>Point</classname> "
"object. The two arguments are also <classname>Point</classname> objects, and "
"we can use the <function>Point.coordinate()</function> function to define "
"the coordinates of the two given points."
msgstr ""
"V funkciji lahko izvedete vse vrste izračunov, ki se vam zdijo potrebni, z "
"uporabo dveh argumentov, če je potrebno. Vrniti bi morali predmet, ki ga "
"želite definirati. V našem primeru je to objekt <classname>Point</"
"classname>. Oba argumenta sta tudi objekta <classname>Point</classname> in "
"lahko uporabimo funkcijo <function>Point.coordinate()</function> za "
"definiranje koordinat dveh danih točk."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The calculation necessary in our example is very simple, we simply add the "
"two sets of coordinates, and divide the new set by two. We then construct a "
"new point using the result. The Python code needed is:"
msgstr ""
"Izračun, potreben v našem primeru, je zelo preprost, preprosto seštejemo dva "
"niza koordinat in novi niz delimo z dva. Nato z rezultatom zgradimo novo "
"točko. Potrebna koda Python je:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:815
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"def calc( a, b ):\n"
"    m = ( a.coordinate() + b.coordinate() ) / 2;\n"
"    return Point( m )"
msgstr ""
"def calc( a, b ):\n"
"    m = ( a.coordinate() + b.coordinate() ) / 2;\n"
"    return Point( m )"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:818
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entering the code"
msgstr "Vnos kode"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:824
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entering the code for the midpoint in the Script Object wizard."
msgstr "Vnos kode za srednjo točko v čarovniku Script Object."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:829
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you now click the <guibutton>Finish</guibutton> button, the new object "
"will appear in the &kig; document. If you move one of the points, the newly "
"created point will move along with it. Much more powerful objects can be "
"built in this way: you are encouraged to try it out."
msgstr ""
"Če zdaj kliknete gumb <guibutton>Dokončaj</guibutton>, se bo nov predmet "
"pojavil v datoteki &kig; dokument. Če premaknete eno od točk, se bo novo "
"ustvarjena točka premaknila skupaj z njo. Na ta način je mogoče zgraditi "
"veliko močnejše predmete: spodbujamo vas, da to preizkusite."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:837
#, no-c-format
msgid "Constructed a Script Object"
msgstr "Konstruirani skriptni predmet"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:843
#, no-c-format
msgid "The newly constructed Script Object."
msgstr "Novo zgrajeni skriptni predmet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:849
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All objects in &kig; can be used in the Python code. As we have seen above, "
"points are of the <classname>Point</classname> class, and you can use &eg; "
"the <function>Point.coordinate()</function> method. You can also return all "
"kinds of objects, not just a <classname>Point</classname>. Many more classes "
"and methods are available in the &kig; Python code, and a more complete "
"reference is provided <ulink url=\"https://edu.kde.org/kig/manual/scripting-"
"api/index.html\">on the &kig; website</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Vsi predmeti v &kig; se lahko uporablja v kodi Python. Kot smo videli "
"zgoraj, so točke razreda <classname>Point</classname> in lahko uporabite "
"&eg; metoda <function>Point.coordinate()</function>. Prav tako lahko vrnete "
"vse vrste objektov, ne le <classname>Point</classname>. Veliko več razredov "
"in metod je na voljo v &kig; kodo Python, popolnejši sklic pa je na voljo "
"<ulink url=\"https://edu.kde.org/kig/manual/scripting-api/index.html\">na "
"spletno mesto &kig;</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:862
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kig; Features"
msgstr "&kig; Zmožnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:866
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; is an open source application. This means that you are free to use and "
"modify it any way you like it. Distributing &kig; is subject to some "
"restrictions, basically that everyone should have the same rights to use "
"&kig;, including your modifications, as you and me."
msgstr ""
"&kig; je odprtokodna aplikacija. To pomeni, da jo lahko prosto uporabljate "
"in spreminjate, kakor želite. Distribucija &kig; je podvržena nekaterim "
"omejitvam, v bistvu, da bi morali imeti vsi enake pravice do uporabe &kig;, "
"vključno z vašimi spremembami, kot vi in jaz."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:873
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Free software programs are developed in a very open spirit, and its "
"developers are usually very responsive to user feedback. Therefore, if you "
"have any questions, complaints, or whatever about &kig;, please contact the "
"kde-edu mailing list at <email>kde-edu@kde.org</email>."
msgstr ""
"Programi proste programske opreme so razviti v zelo odprtem duhu in njihovi "
"razvijalci so običajno zelo odzivni na povratne informacije uporabnikov. "
"Zato, če imate kakršna koli vprašanja, pritožbe ali karkoli o &kig;, se "
"obrnite na poštni seznam kde-edu na <email>kde-edu@kde.org</email>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:882
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; is a KPart application, which means that you can embed it into other "
"&kde; software. If you open a <literal role=\"extension\">.kig</literal> "
"file in &konqueror;, it can be opened directly in the &konqueror; screen "
"without the need to start an external application."
msgstr ""
"&kig; je aplikacija KPart, kar pomeni, da jo lahko vdelate v drugo &kde; "
"programsko opremo. Če datoteko <literal role=\"extension\">.kig</literal> "
"odprete v &konqueror;, jo lahko odprete neposredno v &konqueror; zaslonu, ne "
"da bi bilo treba zagnati zunanjo aplikacijo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:891
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Working with &kig; should be very straightforward. Constructing objects is "
"easy and interactive, with preliminary results being shown, &etc; Moving, "
"selecting and building all work as one would expect them to. Undo support "
"should also be very intuitive."
msgstr ""
"Delo z &kig; mora biti zelo preprosto. Konstruiranje predmetov je enostavno "
"in interaktivno, s prikazanimi predhodnimi rezultati &etc;. Premikanje, "
"izbiranje in gradnja delujejo tako, kot bi pričakovali. Podpora za "
"razveljavitev mora biti tudi zelo intuitivna."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:900
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; supports macros to be defined in a straightforward manner. These "
"objects are presented to the user like normal objects. They are saved on "
"exit and loaded on startup, so that they aren't lost on exit. You can manage "
"these objects in the <guilabel>Manage Types</guilabel> dialog (see <xref "
"linkend=\"working-with-types\"/>). You can export them to files, import them "
"from files, edit and delete them."
msgstr ""
"&kig; podpira makre, ki jih je treba definirati na enostaven način. Ti "
"predmeti so uporabniku predstavljeni kot običajni predmeti. Shranijo se ob "
"izhodu in naložijo ob zagonu, tako da se ob izhodu ne izgubijo. Te objekte "
"lahko upravljate v pogovornem oknu <guilabel>Upravljanje vrst</guilabel> "
"(glejte <xref linkend=\"working-with-types\"/>). Lahko jih izvozite v "
"datoteke, uvozite iz datotek, urejate in brišete."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:912
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kig; saves its data in a clear &XML; format."
msgstr "&kig; shranjuje svoje podatke v jasnem &XML; formatu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:917
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kig; supports the construction of loci."
msgstr "&kig; podpira gradnjo lokusov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:922
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; allows you to export a &kig; file to some interesting formats, like "
"images, <application>XFig</application> and <application>LaTeX</application> "
"files, and &SVG; vectorial images. This is rather useful, because not all "
"programs support the &kig; file format yet."
msgstr ""
"&kig; omogoča izvoz &kig; datoteke v nekaj zanimivih formatov, kot so slike, "
"datoteke <application>XFig</application> in <application>LaTeX</application> "
"ter &SVG; vektorske slike. To je precej koristno, ker vsi programi še ne "
"podpirajo formata datotek &kig;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:931
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kig; has a very flexible transformation system."
msgstr "&kig; ima zelo prilagodljiv sistem transformacije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:936
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kig; aims to be compatible with its competitors. This is why it supports "
"the &kgeo; file format, the &kseg; file format and partially the &drgeo; and "
"&cabri; formats; moreover, support for other formats is planned."
msgstr ""
"&kig; želi biti združljiv s svojimi konkurenti. Zato podpira &kgeo; format "
"datoteke, &kseg; in delno &drgeo; in &cabri; formate; poleg tega je "
"predvidena podpora za druge formate."

